<br>
Ronium:<br>
1) A Sol Cauldron from Lord Searfire in Temple of Solusek Ro.<br>
2) Melatite from model MB or MC clockworks in Sol A.<br>
3) 2 bars of enchanted Platinum.<br>
4) One Mistmoore granite. (in addition to granite for boots)<br>
5) Sands of Ro from Sand Giant in Oasis or So Desert of Ro<br>
6) Soil of Underfoot from Priestess Ghalea in Kaladim Cleric guild.<br>
<br>
Soil of Underfoot:<br>
1) Need 4 faerie dusts and faction.  Do bone chip quest to raise faction.  I hear somewhere in the order of 400 chips need to be turned in.  If you're going after raincaller, have someone else collect dusts.  Don't kill faeries, rangers!<br>
<br>
Temple of Solusek Ro faction:<br>
1) Read following post:<br>
<br>
I am currently trying to gather components for the Ro Armour quests and needed to raise my faction with Lord Searfire in the temple of Solusek Ro. I coned indifferently to him so I could not get the Sol Cauldron that I needed to forge Ronium, the metal needed for the Ro Armour. <br>
<br>
I went to the desert of South Ro to find Rathmana and found him in an orc camp right behind an orc named Ortallius. <br>
<br>
I gave him stack of 3pp in each of the four slots at a time. You are supposed to be able to go from indifferently to amiably with no more than 30pp but I gave him 40pp to be sure. Went back to the temple of Sol Ro and bingo, coned amiably to Lord Searfire and got my Sol Cauldron. <br>
<br>
You don't have to use gold for it to work either. Platinum and gold both work as long as it's 30 gold or 3 platinum. <br>
<br>
Haarkin Trueblade <br>
Paladin of the 23rd season<br>
<br>
Nuff said.  You can also kill shadowed men in lavastorm, WC, or Lesser Faydark for Ro faction.  Be warned, these guys are tough.  I had trouble at lvl 43 with a 37 rogue.  Might want a group if you're in your 30's.<br>
<br>
Note on clockworks.  They will aggro big time, and Sol A is tough.  Thanks to Luni, Gladriel and Llainya who helped out, I was able to get some, but there deaths involved.  They are not aggro unless you attack, though.  So you can walk around them, but once you attack one, they all join in.<br>
<br>
